The View Products for Sale option allows the user to view the current inventory of store items: item IDs, descriptions, department in which the item is located, price, and the quantity available in stock.

The View Low Inventory option shows the user the items which currently have fewer than 100 units available.

The Add to Inventory option allows the user to select a given item ID and add additional inventory to the quantity of the selected item.

The Add New Product option allows the user to enter details about a new product (not presentlt in stock) which will be entered into the database upon completion of the form.

To run the manager interface please follow the steps below:

git clone git@github.com:ngutiboy/bamazondb.git
cd bamazondb
npm install
node bamazondbManager.js

